This paper deals with the study of auction mechanisms, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the optimization of revenue for the auctioneer, which involves the use of algorithms and machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The analysis of bidder behavior and the equilibrium of the auction mechanism involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the design and implementation of auction mechanisms, which falls under the category of computational economics (cs.EC).
